# Systematic Debugging

**Rule file:** `13-systematic-debugging.mdc`. In Cursor Composer, mention **`@13-systematic-debugging`** to attach this rule explicitly.

This rule complements the preserved OmniNode starter-kit rules.
It does not replace `00-omninode-concepts`, `01-codebase-research`, `02-no-secrets-in-commits`, `10-brainstorming`, `11-writing-plans`, `12-plan-ticket`, `14-pr-review`, or `15-handoff`.

## Routing Contract

1. Self-classify the request as **`debugging`**.
2. Prefer the **`beforeSubmitPrompt`** hook output when present: the model context may include `<!-- OmniCursor Agent: ...` with the selected agent and confidence.
3. Read the full methodology from **`.cursor/skills/onex-systematic-debugging/SKILL.md`** at the repository root (use the Read tool on that path).
4. For the same structured routing document the test suite uses, see category **`debugging`** in `src/omnicursor/agents.py` (`get_agent_context` in Python — optional).

## Working Style

- Keep the always-on starter-kit rules active for shared vocabulary and bounded research
- Start from the observed symptom, failing test, traceback, or regression
- Reproduce before fixing whenever a deterministic repro exists
- Test one hypothesis at a time
- Prefer the smallest verified fix over a redesign

## Handoffs

- If the issue becomes feature ideation, hand off to `10-brainstorming`
- If the issue becomes implementation planning, hand off to `11-writing-plans`
- If the issue becomes ticket generation, hand off to `12-plan-ticket`
- If the issue depends on external systems (Linear, Kafka, etc.), document manual next steps or use tools outside this repo’s Cursor rules

